      <hedline>
        <hl1>House of Style</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Gary Pederson letter comments on Jan 18 article about House Speaker Nancy Pelosi's sense of style</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Speaking Chic to Power'' (Thursday Styles, Jan. 18):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Speaking Chic to Power'' (Thursday Styles, Jan. 18):</p>
        <p>Speaker Nancy Pelosi's personal appearance is about style -- not fashion.</p>
        <p>Fashion is a buzz word for follow-the-herd fads. Style is an expression of good taste, individuality and self-confidence.</p>
        <p>The two terms are universes apart.</p>
        <p>Gary Pederson  Edmonton, Alberta, Jan. 18, 2007</p>
      </block>
